9 An Act relating to county purchasing; amending 19
O.S. 2021, Section 1500.1, which relates to the
10 authority of county purchasing agents; authorizing
county purchasing agents to establish online bidding
11 process with certain vendors; updating statutory
language; providing an effective date; and declaring
12 an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 1500.1, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1500.1. A. Except as otherwise provided by Section
19 1500 et seq. of this title, the county purchasing agent shall have
20 the authority to develop, implement, and promote policies and
21 procedures that allow the procurement of materials and equipment
22 through contracts that are flexible, value based and are in the best
23 interests of the state and its political subdivisions.
24
SB752 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 B. Except as otherwise provided, the county purchasing agent
2 shall have the authority to use electronic commerce for the
3 solicitation, notification, and other purchasing processes. For
4 purposes of this subsection, “electronic commerce” means the use of
5 electronic methods to enable solicitations, open bids, supplier
6 response, bid submission, notice of contract award, county
7 acquisition processes, or any other function to make an acquisition.
8 C. The boards of county commissioners shall have the authority
9 to conduct a procurement transaction by electronic means subject to
10 the provisions of the Uniform Electronic Transactions Act.
11 D. The board of county commissioners shall have the authority
12 to establish an online bidding process with a vendor authorized by
13 state contract as provided by the Office of Management and
14 Enterprise Services.
15 1. The purchasing agent shall comply with all bid notice
16 requirements as prescribed in paragraph 2 of subsection B of Section
17 1505 of this title or the Public Competitive Bidding Act of 1974.
18 2. Solicitations shall designate an opening and closing date
19 and time for bids. Sealed bids received pursuant to this subsection
20 shall be first opened in an open meeting of the board of county
21 commissioners concurrently with other sealed bids received as
22 provided in Section 1505 of this title or the Public Competitive
23 Bidding Act of 1974.
24
SB752 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 3. The board of county commissioners shall be authorized to
2 require online bidders to register before the opening date and time
3 and, as part of that registration, require bidders to agree to any
4 terms, conditions, or other requirements of the solicitation or
5 applicable acts.
6 4. The board of county commissioners shall be authorized to
7 require potential online bidders to prequalify as bidders.
8 Solicitations and published bid notices shall indicate the
9 prequalification requirements for online bids. Bids submitted by
10 online bidders not meeting a prequalification requirement shall be
11 disqualified from consideration.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
17
18 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT OVERSIGHT, dated
04/23/2025 - DO PASS.
